headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen scored 25 points, Donovan Mitchell added 24 and the Cleveland Cavaliers held off the Los Angeles Clippers 127-122 on Sunday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jarrett Allen, Donovan Mitchell propel Cavaliers to 127-122 victory over Clippers

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — OG Anunoby and Mikal Bridges each scored 28 points and the New York Knicks dominated the second half for a 110-93 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby and Bridges both score 28 points and Knicks dominate second half to beat Blazers 110-93

headlines.description: — Zaccharie Risacher scored a season-high 36 points, Dyson Daniels added 22 points and five steals while becoming Atlanta's single-season leader, and the Hawks beat the slumping Milwaukee Bucks 145-124 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Risacher scores 36, Daniels sets Hawks' steals record in 145-124 victory over the Bucks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 26 points and eight rebounds and Anthony Edwards added 25 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Detroit Pistons 123-104 on Sunday night in a game that was <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: After 2nd-quarter fight and ejections, Timberwolves beat Pistons 123-104

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jose Alvarado had a go-ahead three-point play on a reverse layup with 31 seconds left and the New Orleans Pelicans outlasted the Charlotte Hornets 98-94 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alvarado has go-ahead 3-point play in the Pelicans' 98-94 win over the Hornets

events.name: Golden State Warriors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Brandin Podziemski scored 27 points and the Golden State Warriors rang up their highest total of the season in a 148-106 rout of the San Antonio Spurs on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Podziemski scores 27 and Warriors have highest point total this season in 148-106 rout of Spurs

headlines.description: — R.J. Barrett scored 31 points and the Toronto Raptors beat Philadelphia 127-109 on Sunday night to send the 76ers to their eighth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett scores 31 points and Raptors win 127-109 to send 76ers to eighth straight loss

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 33 points for Houston, and Phoenix star Kevin Durant left with an ankle injury in the Rockets' 148-109 romp over the Suns on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets rout Suns 148-109 as Phoenix star Durant leaves with ankle injury
